# DISCARD command tests - Discard transaction
@name DISCARD
@group transactions
@since 1.2.0

=== TEST: DISCARD in transaction
RUN:
MULTI
EXPECT:
OK

=== TEST: DISCARD after commands
RUN:
MULTI
SET key "value"
GET key
DISCARD
EXPECT:
QUEUED
QUEUED
OK

=== TEST: DISCARD without MULTI
RUN:
DISCARD
EXPECT:
(error) ERR DISCARD without MULTI

=== TEST: DISCARD clears queue
RUN:
MULTI
SET key1 "value1"
SET key2 "value2"
DISCARD
EXPECT:
QUEUED
QUEUED
OK

=== TEST: DISCARD and verify not executed
RUN:
MULTI
SET mykey "discarded"
DISCARD
EXPECT:
QUEUED
OK

=== TEST: DISCARD multiple operations
RUN:
MULTI
LPUSH mylist "a" "b" "c"
SADD myset "x" "y" "z"
HSET myhash field "value"
DISCARD
EXPECT:
QUEUED
QUEUED
QUEUED
OK

=== TEST: DISCARD wrong number of arguments
RUN:
MULTI
DISCARD extra
EXPECT:
(error) ERR wrong number of arguments for 'discard' command
